  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Archon (Greek: ἄρχων, romanized: árchōn, plural: ἄρχοντες, árchontes) is a Greek word that means \"ruler\", frequently used as the title of a specific public office. It is the masculine present participle of the verb stem αρχ-, meaning \"to be first, to rule\" (see also ἀρχή \"beginning, origin\"), derived from the same root as words such as monarch and hierarchy.",
